            <div class="r-container">
                <div class="row row-cols-lg-1 row-cols-1">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-xs-12 col-md-8 pe-lg-5  order-second">
                        <div class="info-para">
                            <div class="header-block">
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    The critical care department, also known as the intensive care unit (ICU), provides specialized care for patients who are critically ill or injured. Some of the services commonly offered in a critical care department include:
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section position-relative bg-level-1 light-bg-content">
        <div class="section service-section">
            <div class="r-container">
                <div class="row row-cols-lg-1 row-cols-1">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-xs-12 col-md-8 pe-lg-5  order-second">
                        <div class="info-para">
                            <div class="header-block">
                                    <li>
                                    Continuous monitoring of vital signs, such as heart rate, blood pressure, and oxygen saturation
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Mechanical ventilation for patients who require assistance with breathing
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Hemodynamic monitoring to assess cardiac function and blood flow
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Intravenous medications and fluids to support blood pressure and organ function

                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Management of acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS)
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Treatment of sepsis and septic shock
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Renal replacement therapy for patients with kidney failure
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Nutritional support for patients who are unable to eat or drink normally
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Wound care and management
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Pain management and sedation for comfort and healing
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Management of neurological emergencies, such as stroke or traumatic brain injury
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Post-operative care for patients who have undergone complex surgeries
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Continuous assessment and adjustment of treatment plans based on the patient's condition
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Multidisciplinary care involving critical care nurses, physicians, respiratory therapists, pharmacists, and other healthcare professionals
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Family support and communication to keep loved ones informed and involved in the patient's care
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Palliative care for patients with terminal illnesses or those transitioning to end-of-life care
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Rehabilitation planning and coordination for patients recovering from critical illness or injury
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    Transfer coordination for patients who require higher levels of care or specialized services
                                    </li>
                                </ui>
